<center><span style="font-family: Shadows Into Light; font-size: 55px">LEVEL 236: Arsonist Aftermath</span></center><br>
{{Class 2|entity=Low Hostile Entity Count; Environmental Hazards|color-l=4%|color-s=2%}}
{{Blurimage|file=Imageimageimage.png|width=350px|caption=Aerial viewpoint of a part of Level 236.|align=center}}
<div style="font-family: Merriweather">
==<span style="Font-family: Merriweather"> Description </span>==

{{Blurimage|width=250px|file=KirkyBurnham.png|caption=Imagery of Level 236, taken by Kile Burnman on October 26th, 2012.}}
The streets have never been more desolate and lonely within '''Level 236'''. The old, wooden bungalows are charred and burnt, emitting a sulfuric scent that's physically uncomfortable to breathe. Tree vines and moss, overgrown and attached to some of the houses, as nature reclaims what was once human infrastructure. Windows, doors, porches, and roofs, all broken and shattered, with a few barely hanging on. Bullet holes present in the walls of these dilapidated houses. Traces of what had happened—scattered bullet casings, black ash, blood, and rotting tissue—all lay on the dirt roads and fields. The world smells of putrid rot as the occasional corpse appears while wandering down the lane.
{{Blurimage|width=250px|file=CHURCH.jpg|caption=An image of a church in Level 236.|align=left}}
Abandoned churches and chapels are scattered across the map like dots, also decorated with the same charring and mold, similar to the houses. Half-torn posters reciting sacred texts promoting a now-dead religion are taped on the side of the wall, now meaningless and lost to time. Those words would not live to see them passed down.

The old, dusty grandfather clock, still standing tall in the rummage like a survivor in a mere wasteland, struck 7. With that, the village-wide radio systems suddenly crackled to life, the static cutting through the heavy silence like a physical blade. It played heavily distorted choir music and recited the same verses found on the posters, now in the voice of an old woman who sounded as if she had swallowed chalk. Promises of immortality that seemingly never arrived. Sometimes, it inexplicably cuts out for a few seconds.

Remnants of a functional civilization become more prevalent with each step one takes. There were education centers, local stores, rehabilitation hubs, and even agriculture. Empty playgrounds with the swings still in motion, as if the level is trying desperately to feel alive again. Photographs of what seemed like happy families, with their smiling faces vandalized in ash and soot. Empty pits, yet still burning, appear from time to time by the side of the road, but you can never find the source of their fire.

Only in mind, what had happened?

==<span style="Font-family: Merriweather">Hazardous Phenomena</span>==
===<span style="Font-family: Merriweather">Entities</span>===
The entity population has been resurgent within Level 236 after the fall of the Church of Sempiternism, the sole group that used to occupy the level. Commonly seen entities like [[Entity 3|Smilers]], [[Entity 4|Deathmoths]], and [[Entity 2|Windows]] are present and can periodically be encountered, especially at nighttime. In addition to them, level-specific entities have also been confirmed to exist; these are documented below.
<tabber>
|-|Entity File #1=
<big> > ENTITY FILE 1: GRAVEKEEPERS</big>

<div style="background: #000000; border: 2px solid #FFFFFF; border-radius: 0px; padding: 30px 20px; margin: 5px 10px; color: #FFFFFF; margin-bottom: 20px; overflow: hidden">
{{Blurimage|file=Screenshot 2026-04-17 215932.png|caption=Still frame from a found footage of a floating Gravekeeper in Level 236 beside a redacted corpse.|width=370px}}
'''Gravekeepers''', also known as '''The Unworthy''' are entities exclusively found on Level 236. They are described as approximately 7 feet tall, spindly, incorporeal humanoid creatures with out-of-place facial features. They are rarely seen standing on the ground; most encounters happen while they're either kneeling, sitting, or floating. Their activity peaks at 8:00 PM - 9:00 PM, when auditory hallucinations usually happen (see below).

Gravekeepers are always seen next to a corpse, or the remnants of one, and are highly protective of it. Approaching a Gravekeeper usually makes one's mental state gradually more dreadful and grief-stricken, often amplifying existing unpleasant memories of the observer, or potentially even implanting unpleasant memories that don't exist if one is within extreme proximity. Despite their threatening psychological presence, they are dormant and pose no physical threat to wanderers, even if one attempts to attack them.

Hostility usually happens only when one provokes or disturbs the corpse a Gravekeeper is protecting. When one performs this act, the entity will transition from a stationary, dormant state to a malevolent state, subsequently hunting them down relentlessly until either the wanderer is tormented and killed or successfully escapes. Afterwards, it will tend to float back to its original location and keep overseeing the corpse. Yet, it will continue attacking once it is notified of the wanderer's presence again if the wanderer has survived the previous encounter.

However, there is a limited number of Gravekeepers in Level 236, as Gravekeepers do not protect corpses that have died on Level 236 after the year 2011. The reason for this particularity remains a mystery. The exact population is unknown, but it is speculated that there are over 50 Gravekeepers scattered across Level 236, each guarding its own carcass.

To survive a Gravekeeper encounter, one must simply ignore it and walk as far away from it as possible. If one must walk close to it, however, try to act as boring as possible, and be careful with handling the corpse, as a Gravekeeper might be mourning. Finally, just don't pity it.
</div>

|-|Entity File #2=
<big> > ENTITY FILE 2: LUNAWATCHERS </big>

<div style="background: #000000; border: 2px solid #FFFFFF; border-radius: 0px; padding: 30px 20px; margin: 5px 10px; color: #FFFFFF; margin-bottom: 20px; overflow: hidden">
{{Blurimage|file=Screenshot 2026-01-31 195759.png|width=289px|caption=Another still footage, this time of a Virtue within Level 236.}}
'''Lunawatchers''' are entities that infrequently materialize in Level 236. They are jaggedly round, cyclopic, sentient spheres that are covered in layers of flesh, muscles, and nerves. They appear in the sky, often seemingly replacing the stars according to anecdotal reports, usually when the wanderer is not observing the sky or when one blinks while observing it. Only one Virtue can be present every night.

During their dormant state, their appearance is what is described above. Rarely, however, do they go into their stalking state. This state isn't necessarily life-threatening, but it can be dread-inducing. Initially, their flesh layers will unravel into an eye-like shape. However, it will be immediately shown that they have no eyes in the traditional sense, but rather a dark, limitless oblivion. Subsequently, any wanderer within the immediate vicinity will hear an uncomfortably high-pitched screeching, supposedly coming from it. While travelling Level 236 at this time, one will feel surveilled and judged by a mysterious, omnipresent force, and will constantly be in a state of high anxiety and alert.

The voided eye of a Virtue is also incredibly cognitohazardous. Looking at the eye for extended periods can cause nausea, mild headaches, dizziness, and the temporary loss of cognitive abilities or muscle memory. After this initial phase of discomfort, the anxiety of being watched will intensify significantly, causing more stress and, in extreme cases, PTSD.

Surviving a Virtue is relatively simple, as its effects are not deeply life-threatening. If one sees the stars fading away and the sky shifting, it is advised to look at the ground for the rest of one's travel, or take shelter inside a house (beware of structural integrity, however).
</div>
|-|Entity File #3=
<big> > ENTITY FILE 3: PROPHETS </big>
<div style="background: #000000; border: 2px solid #FFFFFF; border-radius: 0px; padding: 30px 20px; margin: 5px 10px; color: #FFFFFF; margin-bottom: 20px; overflow: hidden">
{{Blurimage|file=tt.jpg|width=350px|caption=An image of a Prophet captured in the streets of Level 236.}}
'''Prophets''' are humanoid entities found in Level 236. They are the rarest to encounter of the three previous entities. Their appearance is of a hairless, skin-pale figure lacking eyeballs, only leaving the sockets intact. They are commonly seen in clean, white robes, a juxtaposition to their unnatural figure. Additionally, they are normally seen with wings at the back of their body or a halo floating above their head.

Unlike previous entities, Prophets are actively malicious. They are usually seen descending from the sky as clouds separate, and a light shines down onto the surface. Furthermore, one in proximity to a Prophet will start hearing holy messages, slowly replacing any other thoughts in their mind. After they have been fully subjugated, a Prophet will proceed to steal their essence of life, leaving them dead while their physical body still functions normally. However, death does not mean the body stops functioning. Even if a person is spiritually dead, their body will continue to move towards the horizon. Attempts to save victims or prevent them from going to the horizon are fruitless.

When one notices an instance of a Prophet descending from the sky, it is heavily advised to evacuate the immediate area or carefully hide in a dark place. If one is under the mental effects of a Prophet, try to fight it as hard as possible. This can be done by reciting personal events or messages, quotes from works of literature, or imaginary scenarios.
</div>
