''Chronicles of Divine Art 5:17, Book of the Great Artist''

...And thou shalt love thy prophet as much as thou dost love the Canvas and me, for they bear the holy message I am willing to spread. They are a son of mine, and you are a son of them, and they will lead you to greatness, just as I did to them.

The Prophet is the Canvas made flesh. To look upon him, to look upon his voice, is to observe the Masterpiece. He who ignores the Prophet ignores the Canvas, for the Canvas has no voice but his. He who ignores shall be considered blasphemous and left forgotten by the punishment of death, whereas those who seek and listen shall be rewarded with eternal beauty.
</div>

